Business Problem
A multinational technology organization has observed an increase in employee attrition over the past few years. To better understand the factors influencing employee turnover and to prepare for future predictive analytics initiatives, the Human Resources (HR) Analytics team has consolidated employee demographic, employment, compensation, performance, learning, and employee survey data from multiple internal systems.

Before predictive models can be developed, the organization requires a comprehensive feature engineering pipeline to transform the raw data into a machine learning-ready dataset. As a Data Scientist, your responsibility is to explore the dataset, identify data quality issues, engineer meaningful features, and prepare the data for downstream modelling.

The dataset provided is synthetic but has been designed to closely resemble a realistic enterprise HR dataset. It contains characteristics commonly observed in real-world datasets, including missing values, skewed distributions, outliers, correlated features, and redundant variables.

Your task is to design an effective feature engineering pipeline by making appropriate preprocessing decisions and providing clear technical justification for every major step.

Important Note

This assignment is designed to evaluate your understanding of feature engineering concepts and your ability to apply them appropriately to a real-world problem.

There is no single correct solution for this assignment. Multiple technically sound approaches are acceptable, provided they are supported by appropriate analysis and justification.

Students are encouraged to make independent feature engineering decisions based on the characteristics of the dataset.

Marks will be awarded based on the quality of analysis, justification for decisions, and overall effectiveness of the feature engineering pipeline.

Assignment Objective

The objective of this assignment is to apply feature engineering techniques to prepare a real-world style HR dataset for future machine learning applications.

You are expected to analyze the dataset, identify data quality issues, make appropriate feature engineering decisions, construct meaningful features, evaluate feature selection and dimensionality reduction techniques, and develop a reusable preprocessing pipeline.

This assignment emphasizes decision-making, reasoning, and justification rather than simply applying feature engineering techniques.


Dataset Description

The dataset contains employee demographic, employment, compensation, performance, learning, and employee engagement information collected from multiple HR systems within a multinational technology organization. It has been created to simulate a realistic enterprise HR analytics dataset for feature engineering tasks.

Each row represents one employee.

The dataset consists of 5,000 employee records and 39 variables, including the target variable (Attrition).

Target Variable:

The target variable is Attrition, where:

0 – Employee Stayed
1 – Employee Left
