Assignment Tasks

Part A – Understanding the Dataset (4 Marks)

Objective

Explore the dataset to understand its structure and identify characteristics that may impact downstream machine learning tasks.

Directions

Your analysis should include:

Identify feature types and summarize the dataset.
Examine numerical distributions and relationships using appropriate visualizations.
Identify missing values, outliers, skewed variables, and other data quality issues.
Summarize key observations that will influence your feature engineering decisions.
Expected Deliverables

Exploratory data analysis with supporting visualizations.
Summary of key observations and identified data quality issues.
Part B – Designing a Feature Engineering Strategy (6 Marks)

Objective

Prepare the dataset for machine learning by applying appropriate feature engineering techniques.

Directions

Your work should include:

Handle missing values and other data quality issues.
Apply suitable preprocessing and transformations to numerical and categorical variables.
Justify every major feature engineering decision.
Briefly discuss alternative approaches where appropriate.
Expected Deliverables

Feature-engineered dataset after preprocessing.
Justification for the techniques applied.
Part C – Feature Construction & Feature Selection (4 Marks)

Objective

Improve the dataset by creating meaningful features and selecting the most relevant variables.

Directions

Your work should include:

Construct meaningful new features using existing variables.
Explain the business intuition behind the engineered features.
Identify redundant, highly correlated, or less informative features.
Justify your feature selection decisions.
Expected Deliverables

List of engineered features with justification.
Final selected feature set.
Part D – Dimensionality Reduction & Pipeline Design (4 Marks)

Objective

Evaluate whether dimensionality reduction is appropriate and develop a reusable preprocessing pipeline.

Directions

Your work should include:

Assess whether dimensionality reduction is beneficial.
Apply and interpret the technique, if appropriate.
Develop a reusable preprocessing pipeline integrating all feature engineering steps.
Expected Deliverables

Justification for dimensionality reduction.
Reusable preprocessing pipeline.
Part E – Summary & Reflection (2 Marks)

Objective

Summarize the overall feature engineering process and key decisions.

Directions

Provide a brief summary covering:

Important feature engineering decisions.
Challenges encountered.
Benefits of the final preprocessing pipeline.
Assumptions or limitations, if any.
Expected Deliverables

A concise summary of your overall approach and findings.

Evaluation Criteria

Students will be graded primarily on:

Correct application of feature engineering concepts.
Logical reasoning behind feature engineering decisions.
Clarity, organization, and technical quality of explanations.
Ability to develop a coherent and reusable feature engineering pipeline.
Simplicity with strong technical justification will receive higher credit than unnecessarily complex solutions with limited reasoning.

Students will NOT be graded on:

Machine learning model accuracy.
Achieving the highest predictive performance.
Using the maximum number of feature engineering techniques.

